Windows Installation
--------------------

Download the most recent ".jar" file, then put it into the "plugins"
folder of the ImageJ distribution. By default, this folder is:

C:\Program Files\ImageJ\plugins\


Linux Installation
------------------

Download the most recent ".jar" file, then put it into the following
folder:

~/.imagej/plugins/


Building from source
====================

You will first have to install CMake (http://www.cmake.org/) and, of
course, ImageJ. Here are the commands to build from source under
Linux:

# mkdir Build
# cd Build
# cmake ..
# make
